      <item>
        <title>Adding Column Or More To An Existed Table In Rails</title>
        <description>&lt;p&gt;TAGS:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&lt;pre class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;code&gt;ruby  rails  migration  database  add 
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;h3&gt;Adding Column Or More To An Existed Table.&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The general form of &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;adding&lt;/code&gt; field to table is:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rails&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;migration&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;AddColumnnameToTablename&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;columnname&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:datatype&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example, Adding &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;price&lt;/code&gt; column to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;books&lt;/code&gt; table:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then, &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Columnname = Price&lt;/code&gt;
and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Tablename = Books&lt;/code&gt;
and &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;datatype = float&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rails&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;migration&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;AddPriceToBooks&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;price&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:float&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rake&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;db&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:migrate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If you need to add &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;many&lt;/code&gt; columns to table you can use:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rails&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;migration&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;AddDetailsToBooks&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;pages&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:integer&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;year&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:integer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Then,&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rake&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;db&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:migrate&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that you can undo this migration back step by step using:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rake&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;db&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:rollback&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will delete the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;price&lt;/code&gt; column from the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;books&lt;/code&gt; table in the database itself.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;color:red;&quot;&gt;Note, Any &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;rake db:rollback&lt;/code&gt; may delete stored data in the &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;targeted&lt;/code&gt; columns and can’t be restored again.&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, You can delete the migration file generated by converting &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;g&lt;/code&gt;(for generate) to &lt;code class=&quot;highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;d&lt;/code&gt; (for destroy) in migration command as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-ruby&quot; data-lang=&quot;ruby&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rails&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;g&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;AddPriceToBooks&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;price&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:float&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;#to be&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;rails&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;no&quot;&gt;AddPriceToBooks&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;price&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;ss&quot;&gt;:float&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The last line will delete the migration file generted by the first line.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Take a look to this tutorial video:&lt;/p&gt;

